node.text:
Kali the lioness must protect her cubs from all sorts of dangers in the Serengeti, but did she ever think she would have to protect them from her own pride?

In Serengeti II, there are new characters and fresh rivalries in the same spectacular setting. Return to an unspoilt corner of Africa’s Serengeti for more real-life animal drama.
Find out more via the link in our bio

Meet the kung fu master 👀

Mantids are born with excellent eyesight. However, their keen eyes are no equal match for that of a hungry jumping spider. But they do have one trick up their sleeve when it comes to self-defence: partaking in a bit of kung-fu. This self-defence mechanism serves to confuse its predator, making the insect appear bigger than it actually is. But, the fight to stay alive doesn’t end there…

My face hearing gossip 😲⁣
⁣
Caracals (Caracal caracal) have over 20 muscles in their large pointed ears, with signature tufts that help to funnel in sounds.⁣

⁣
Marmots (Marmota marmota) live in burrows and can dig through tough terrain. They will hibernate in these burrows for up to 9 months per year.⁣
⁣

Hiding from deadlines 👀⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Japanese flying dwarf squirrels (Pteromys momonga) are nocturnal, and spend their days in nests or tree cavities, before emerging at dusk to hunt for food.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#EarthCapture by @bonny_animal ⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣

node.text:
Perfect pompom plumage
⁣
This striking avian beauty is an Andean cock-of-the-rock (Rupicola peruvianus). They can be found in the forests of the Andes mountain range in South America.⁣
⁣
BONUS FACT: they are the national bird of Peru⁣.
⁣
#EarthCapture by @andres.vasquez.n⁣
.⁣⁣⁣

Moose are the largest living members of the deer family. Male moose, or bulls, are easily identified by their huge antlers. 🦌⁣
⁣
#Eden: Untamed Planet explores some of the world's most isolated landscapes. Each episode embarks on a journey to Earth's last Edens, including Southeast Alaska, an ice-bound Eden that harbours possibly the richest temperate rainforests of all. ⁣

⁣
These little ones are born blind at birth, and it takes roughly 10 days for their eyes to open.

node.text:

⁣
The king bird-of-paradise (Cicinnurus regius) is hard to miss with its fabulous array of vivid colours. They are particularly noisy birds too, using loud calls to mark their territory. ⁣
